# 8. 初めての握手会

Guide A: Thank you for joining us today! Please move forward in an orderly manner!
Haruka: It's turning out to be a good crowd.
Shizuku: Yes, and all of the staff seem so motivated about making sure everything goes well!
Airi: Got our schedule down, Minori?
Minori: Yup! We'll start with a Christmas talk show that includes some of our own experiences, a meet and greet, and a mini-concert to cap it all off!
Airi: Sounds about right. It's good to see that you're not letting your nerves get the better of you. Looks like the Fan Festival's done wonders for you!
Shizuku: Hehe. It certainly has. Let's all do everything we can to make this event a success!
Minori: Yeah!
Minori, Haruka, Shizuku & Airi: MORE MORE JUMP!
Minori: Merry Christmas, everyone! We're MORE MORE JUMP!
Haruka: Thank you for being here today!
Fans: MORE MORE JUMP!'s the best!!
Fans: They're so cute!!
Minori: O-Oh wow...! There are so many people in the audience...!!
Minori: L-Let's jump right into the first part of our event...! The “MMJ Christmas Talk Show!”
Haruka, Shizuku & Airi: Yay!!
Lighting Technician A: Make sure to cut out after the second song! After that, just wait for the signal to turn the stage lights back on!
Lighting Technician B: Copy that!
Haruka: (Good, that was perfectly timed...)
Airi: (Nice work! I'm glad we practiced that part!)
Minori & Shizuku: ♪————!
Minori: (The smiles on our fans' faces are sparkling, and they're cheering their hearts out...!)
Minori: (I must be dreaming...! But this isn't a dream...)
Minori: (This is all happening because we came together to build this from the ground up...!!)
Minori: Okay... Next is the meet and greet.
Airi: Yeah, but...
Minori: Wah...! So many people...!
Haruka: The fans don't really seem to know where to line up.
Airi: We only have a few guides and they already have their hands full. If this keeps up, we might need to step in...
Minori: R-Right...
Yuina: Please form a single-file line, everybody!!!
Fans: Wah! So loud!
Fans: Who was that? Where are they?
Yuina: The end of Minori's line is here! Please make sure to stay within the hall as much as possible!!
Yuina: You all still have plenty of time! You'll all be able to meet everyone from MORE MORE JUMP! Please proceed in an orderly manner!
Fans: Oh, the orange placard! That must be the line for Minori!
Fans: And the blue one's for Haruka, right?
Crowd Controllers: She's not on the crowd control team, but she's helping us anyway? That means I need to keep trying too!
Shizuku: Look, all the fans are starting to move...
Minori: That's amazing! The staff are working really hard to make sure they form neat lines...!
Haruka: You can thank them later, Minori. We should take this chance to move to the meet-and-greet booths.
Minori: Okay!
Haruka's Fan: H-Haruka...! It's so great to see you again!! I'm so happy that you decided to become an idol again...!
Haruka: Thank you... Oh, didn't we meet at the dome concert two years ago...?
Haruka's Fan: What?! Y-You remember me?!
Haruka: Of course. You mentioned that you live in Okinawa. I still have that postcard you sent me on display in my living room.
Haruka: I'd like to give you a little Christmas present in return. I hope you like it...
Haruka's Fan: Haruka... I'll treasure it forever...!
Airi's Fan: I saw the event you guys did at the elementary school, Airi! That was so much fun!
Airi: You did? Thanks!
Airi's Fan: Always! I just want to say that I've been a huge fan since you were with QT and on all those variety shows...
Airi's Fan: Getting to see Happy Everyday again made me so happy!
Airi: Heh heh heh. I appreciate your kind words...
Airi's Fan: *Gasp*...! That mask...!
Airi: It's Happy Everyday! Thank you for your support. I hope we get to see more of each other!
Shizuku: Thank for you coming to see us today. Have you been enjoying the show?
Shizuku's Fan: Yes! I can't believe I'm shaking hands with you like this... I must be dreaming!
Shizuku's Fan: Um... I always loved seeing the perfect Shizuku Hinomori of Cheerful * Days...
Shizuku's Fan: But getting to see you in a new light with MORE MORE JUMP! has been so exciting too...
Shizuku's Fan: And I definitely like the current you more. We get to see the real you now, so I'm really glad that you joined MORE MORE JUMP!
Shizuku: *Gasp*...! Thank you so much.
Minori: (Whoa...! The number of fans lining up for those three is incredible...!)
Yuina: Minori, you have fans waiting!
Minori: Huh?! S-Sorry! Wait, fans...?
Yuina: Yes, quite a few are waiting in line! I hope you're ready for them!
Minori: M-My fans...?!
Minori: (That's right. I'm an idol who can spread hope to others now...)
Minori: (I still don't really feel like one yet, but does this mean I can be just like my heroes from when I was growing up? A real idol?)
Minori: (No, don't say whether or not you can. I will become that idol!)
Minori: Hello! Thank you for joining us today!!
Haruka: (Hehe. Looks like Minori's having fun.)
Haruka: (I'm so glad that we were able to put on this event...)
Announcement: <This concludes the MORE MORE JUMP! Christmas Fan Event.>
Announcement: <Please make sure not to leave anything behind on your way out.>
Fans: That was really fun! Seeing MORE MORE JUMP! live was so cool!
Fans: I know, right? To be fair, I was pretty scared about what would happen after they started recruiting fans to work as staff... But everything went great!
Fans: Yeah, I really want to see them again! Maybe I'll join on as staff next time!
Airi: Phew... That's it. Our event's over. Nice work today, everyone!
Staff: Nice work!!
Minori: Thank you all very much for being here today! We really appreciate it!
Haruka: We can't express our gratitude enough. This event was able to succeed because of you, so again, thank you.
Shizuku: And we've prepared some presents for each of you as a token of our appreciation. I hope you'll be willing to accept them.
Staff A: Are these handkerchiefs...? With our initials stitched in?!
Shizuku: We had a discussion about how we can make this moment feel special, and we decided to make something for you in our spare time.
Airi: Shizuku really has a talent for embroidery! The rest of us made you some snacks to go with your present!
Minori: We all put a lot of effort into making these, so we really hope that you like them!
Staff: Yay! This is so awesome!
Saito: There's actually something we'd like to present to you as well, MORE MORE JUMP!
Haruka: Present to us?
Saito: Yes! Ready, everyone? One, two...
Saito, Yuina & Staff: Minori, Haruka, Airi, Shizuku! Congratulations on a successful first event!
Minori: Oh wow...!
Shizuku: Such a beautiful bouquet...!
Staff A: Um... I actually applied to work as staff for today because I just wanted a chance to see all of you up close...
Staff B: Me too. I didn't realize that working on something like this would be so hard, and I was worried that we wouldn't get everything set up in time...
Staff B: But seeing all of you putting so much effort into it gave me the motivation to keep going!
Saito: Helping MORE MORE JUMP! spread so much hope to others really turned out to be a great experience! Thank you!!
Yuina: You four are our favorite idols and genuinely lifted our spirits today! I'll never forget what happened today!
Minori: You guys...
Minori: I-I'll never forget...! Thank you so much!
Haruka: ...
KAITO: It'll be a special experience for them since they'll get to see their favorite idols smile by making their event a success.
Minori: But this is what I really think!
Minori: Fans don't just want to see idols shine and sparkle.
Minori: Fans will be there to support their favorite idols through thick and thin! They'll cheer for them no matter what if it means they'll keep shining!
Haruka: (Thank you, KAITO. Thank you, Minori...)
Haruka: (Without you both, I never would've been able to experience this sensation.)
Haruka: It was wonderful putting this event together with all of you. From the bottom of my heart, thank you...
Minori: Thank goodness our event ended up going so well!
Airi: I know, right? And I love how they surprised us with this giant bouquet at the end!
Airi: I was worried about what would happen at first, but putting on events with our fans like this might be a good way to go for us...
Haruka: Hehe. I agree.
Minori: C-Can I just say something?!
Minori: I'd like to do this again! I want to put on another event that puts smiles on our fans' faces!
Airi: Me too. I didn't realize that working on something like this would be so hard, and I was worried that we wouldn't get everything set up in time...
Shizuku: That means we'll have to start expanding our song repertoire.
Haruka: That'd be great. Why don't we start discussing what we'll be doing the next time we meet?
Minori: Yeah!
Minori: (A lot's happened along the way, but I've gone from being a Haruka admirer to being an idol just like the others...)
Minori: (On top of that, we were able to work with our fans to put on an unforgettable event! I couldn't be happier!)
Minori: (I always thought that idols were the only ones who could spread hope to others...)
Minori: (But I realize now that our fans can also be just as powerful a source of hope.)
Minori: (Which means I'm gonna need to keep trying harder and harder! I need to spread more and more hope to return the favor!)
Minori: (And I have to keep growing as an idol for that to happen...!)
Minori: Yeah... Tomorrow, I'm gonna keep trying more and more!!
